Show bashly reference documentation

This command displays bite-sized help for all the bashly configuration options
in the terminal.

Usage:
  bashly doc [SEARCH] [--index]
  bashly doc (-h|--help)

Options:
  -i --index
    Show option keys only

  -h --help
    Show this help

Parameters:
  SEARCH
    Search for options that match this text

Examples:
  bashly doc command
  bashly doc command.flags
  bashly doc flag. -i
  bashly doc catch_all
